# @zyrab/domo-og

Dynamic Open Graph image generator for use with [domo-ssg](https://github.com/Zyrab/Domo/tree/main/packages/domo-ssg). It takes an SVG template, replaces template variables (like `{{title}}`), and converts the result into a PNG using `resvg`.

## Features

- Simple `{{title}}` substitution in SVG templates
- Converts SVG to PNG using fast and accurate `resvg` binary
- Uses platform-specific `resvg` binaries (v0.45.1)
- Stores temp SVGs in OS-level temporary directory

## Usage

```js
import { generateOgImage } from "@zyrab/domo-og";

await generateOgImage({
  slug: "my-blog-post", // Used for filename
  outputDir: "./public/og/", // PNG destination
  svgTemplate: "./assets/og-template.svg",
  title: "My Blog Post Title",
});
```

Ensure your SVG template has a placeholder like:

```xml
<text>{{title}}</text>
```

## Notes

- Only `{{title}}` replacement is supported for now.
- Resvg binaries are bundled under bin/{linux,darwin,win32}/.

